### Step 10: Production Graduation Criteria

A factor graduates from research to the production factor library when it meets **all** of the following:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    GRADUATION CHECKLIST                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ □ ICIR > 0.3 on validation set (2021–2023)                 │
│ □ ICIR > 0.2 on test set (2024+) — out-of-sample           │
│ □ Quantile spread is monotonic in both train and test       │
│ □ Factor survives industry + size neutralization            │
│ □ Correlation < 0.5 with all existing production factors    │
│ □ Turnover is reasonable for target rebalance frequency     │
│ □ Results logged in MLflow with experiment ID               │
│ □ Factor code has docstring, formula, data source           │
│ □ PIT compliance verified (no lookahead bias)               │
│ □ Factor tested across CSI300, CSI500, and all_stocks       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Once graduated, implement the factor in `src/alpha_research/factor_library/{category}/` following the naming convention and documentation standards in [research-integrity.md](file:///e:/%E9%87%8F%E5%8C%96%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F/.agents/rules/research-integrity.md) §5.

